---
import SiteLayout from "@/layouts/main.astro";
import CtaCard from "@/components/cta-card.astro";
import { wpasset } from "@/lib/wordpress/utils";

const heroImage = wpasset("2026/06/about-page-hero.png");
const storyImage = wpasset("2026/06/about-page-section2.png");
const sectionThreeImage = wpasset("2026/06/about-page-section3.png");
const ctaImage = wpasset("2026/06/about-us-cta.png");
---

<SiteLayout>
  <section class="page-content grid gap-10 py-10 md:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr] md:items-center md:py-14">
    <div>
      <h1 class="max-w-xl text-[34px] font-black uppercase leading-[0.96] text-black md:text-[44px]">
        Born From A Lifelong Passion For Reptiles
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-[#333] md:text-lg">
        We're a small family breeder focused on raising healthy ball pythons with
        care and intention.
      </p>
    </div>

    <img
      src={heroImage}
      alt="Steele Pythons family"
      class="ml-auto w-full max-w-[360px] rounded-sm object-cover"
    />
  </section>

  <section class="page-content pb-16">
    <h2 class="text-[30px] font-black uppercase leading-none text-black md:text-[40px]">
      Our Story
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-[#252525] md:text-lg">
      <p>
        Like many in this hobby, my love for reptiles started at a young age. My
        first real reptile was a normal ball python I picked up while I was in
        college. As most keepers will tell you, it's nearly impossible to stop at
        just one. Before long, the collection began to grow - blood pythons,
        Dumeril's boas, a Burmese python, and of course, more ball pythons. My wife
        and I even spent a few years keeping leopard geckos as part of our growing
        reptile family.
      </p>

      <p>
        Eventually, life moved forward. Marriage and kids brought new
        responsibilities, and I no longer had the time I wanted to properly dedicate
        to my animals, so I stepped away from the hobby for a while.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[1fr_0.95fr] md:items-center">
      <div class="space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-[#252525] md:text-lg">
        <p>
          When my oldest son was three, we visited a local reptile show and picked
          up a normal male ball python from a breeder we met there. That breeder
          kindly gave my son a t-shirt to go along with our new pet. Fast forward
          about 8-9 years later, and my youngest was wearing that same shirt. That
          moment led me to look the breeder up - and I was surprised to see just how
          far he had come in the hobby.
        </p>

        <p>That breeder was Justin Kobylka.</p>
      </div>

      <img
        src={storyImage}
        alt="Child with ball python"
        class="w-full rounded-sm object-cover"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-content pb-16">
    <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] md:items-center">
      <img
        src={sectionThreeImage}
        alt="Reptile education presentation"
        class="w-full rounded-sm object-cover"
      />

      <div class="space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-[#252525] md:text-lg">
        <p>
          From there, things really started to grow. What began as a return to a
          long-lost passion has now evolved into a focused journey toward breeding
          ball pythons responsibly and intentionally. We're currently breeding many
          snakes and have exciting things coming!
        </p>

        <p>
          Our goal is simple: produce healthy, well-started animals and stay
          grounded in the care and respect these animals deserve.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-content pb-16">
    <CtaCard
      title="Interested In One Of Our Ball Pythons?"
      body="We're happy to answer questions and help you find the right fit."
      image={ctaImage}
      buttonLabel="Contact"
    />
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
